tion as the crisis intensified in september  creation of gsamp trust sedit on october   as the crisis had begun to unravel allan sloan a senior editor for fortune magazine wrote so lets reduce this macro story to human scale meet gsamp trust s a  million drop in the junkmortgage bucket part of the more than halfatrillion dollars of mortgagebacked securities issued last year we found this issue by asking mortgage mavens to pick the worst deal they knew of that had been floated by a toptier firm – and this ones pretty bad it was sold by goldman sachs – gsamp originally stood for goldman sachs alternative mortgage products but now has become a name itself like att and m this issue which is backed by ultrarisky secondmortgage loans contains all the elements that facilitated the housing bubble and bust its got speculators searching for quick gains in hot housing markets its got loans that seem to have been made with little or no serious analysis by lenders and finally its got wall street which churned out mortgage product because buyers wanted it as they say on the street when the ducks quack feed them conversion to a bank holding companyedit on september   goldman sachs and morgan stanley the last two major investment banks in the united states both confirmed that they would become traditional bank holding companies the federal reserves approval of their bid to become banks ended the business model of an independent securities firm  years after congress separated them from deposittaking lenders and capped weeks of chaos that sent lehman brothers into bankruptcy and led to the rushed sale of merrill lynch  co to bank of america corp reputation tarnishededit according to a  brandasset valuator survey taken of  people nationwide the firms reputation suffered in  and  and rival morgan stanley was respected more than goldman sachs a reversal of the sentiment in  goldman refused to comment on the findings tarp and berkshire hathaway investment edit on september   berkshire hathaway agreed to purchase  billion in goldmans preferred stock and also received warrants to buy another  billion in goldmans common stock within  years the company also raised  billion via a public offering of shares at  per share goldman also received a  billion preferred stock investment from the us treasury in october  as part of the troubled asset relief program tarp andrew cuomo then new york attorney general questioned goldmans decision to pay  employees bonuses of at least  million each after it received tarp funds in  that same period however ceo lloyd blankfein and  other senior executives opted to forgo bonuses stating they believed it was the right thing to do in light of the fact that we are part of an industry thats directly associated with the ongoing economic distress cuomo called the move appropriate and prudent and urged the executives of other banks to follow the firms lead and refuse bonus payments in june  goldman sachs repaid the us treasurys tarp investment with  interest in the form of  million in preferred dividend payments and  billion in warrant redemptions on march   goldman sachs acquired federal reserve approval to buy back berkshires preferred stock in goldman in december  goldman announced that its top  executives will be paid yearend bonuses in restricted stock that they cannot sell for  years with clawback provisions use of federal reserves emergency liquidity programs edit during the  financial crisis the federal reserve introduced a number of shortterm credit and liquidity facilities to help stabilize markets some of the transactions under these facilities provided liquidity to institutions whose disorderly failure could have severely stressed an already fragile financial system goldman sachs was one of the heaviest users of these loan facilities taking out many loans between march   and april   the primary dealer credit facility pdcf the first fed facility ever to provide overnight loans to investment banks loaned goldman sachs a total of  billion against collateral such as corporate market instruments and mortgagebacked securities the term securities lending facility tslf which allows primary dealers to borrow liquid treasury securities for one month in exchange for less liquid collateral loaned goldman sachs a total of  billion goldman sachss borrowings totaled  billion in hundreds of revolving transactions over these months the loans were fully repaid in accordance with the terms of the facilities acquisition of remainder of jbwereedit in  goldman took full control of jbwere in a  billion buyout shut down of global alpha hedge fund edit in  goldman sachs shut down the global alpha fund once the firms largest hedge funds the announcement followed a reported decline in fund balances to less than  billion in june  from  billion in  the decline was caused by investors withdrawing from the fund following earlier substantial market losses global alpha was at one point one of the largest hedge funds in the world with over  billion under management it was started in  with  million acquisition of business from deutsche bank edit in september  goldman sachs asset management announced it had entered into an agreement with deutsche asset  wealth management to acquire its stable value business with total assets under supervision of  billion as of june   apples  billion bond offering edit in april  together with deutsche bank goldman led a  billion bond offering by apple inc the largest corporatebond deal in history was apples first since  goldman sachs managed both of apples previous bond offerings in the s twitter initial public offering edit goldman sachs was the lead underwriter for twitters initial public offering in  at the time goldmans position as lead underwriter for twitter was considered one of the biggest tech prizes around goldman earned approximately  million in fees from the twitter ipo however the chief economist and strategist at zt wealth said goldman being the first name on the s ha